English translation: Plate.

Point of interest: this is the Old French root of ''omelette''. (<--add cross reference)

Origin: 1605–15; < F omelette, earlier ''amelette'', metathetic form of ''alemette'', var. of ''alemelle'' lit., thin plate, var. of OF ''lemelle'' < L ''lāmella''.

